œÑt = œÑr‚àí1 + œÑs‚àí1 + œÑi‚àí1 ‚àí1, (50)

where œÑi is the correlation time for internal motion. These equations are valid for isotropically tumbling systems; otherwise, the angles between the principal axes of the diffusion tensor and PRE vector must be taken into account (Benetis & Kowalewski, 1985; Woessner, 1962).

