Page 32

If the exchange between states A and B is not fast on the PRE timescale (i.e. if ex ‚â´ Œì2,B ‚àí Œì2,A is not true), the apparent PRE is not simply a population-averaged value, but is instead intermediate between Œì2,A and the population-averaged value (Fig. 2c). Under these conditions of slower exchange, the apparent PRE can be calculated using the McConnell
equations (McConnell, 1958). These necessary equations are identical to the general
equations for chemical exchange (Eqs. (16)‚Äì(20)), except the relaxation matrix R (Eq. (18))
includes the PRE from each state, taking the form (for two-site exchange):

R=

