Page 43

Adjacent side chains can also be allowed to move to resolve steric overlap with the tag. At
each step, Xplor-NIH will recalculate the order parameter for each PRE vector from the
position of the different members of the tag ensemble. Fitting also requires the specification
of correlation times, which can be explicitly provided or fit along with the tag positions in Xplor-NIH. If using the SB mode (i.e. Eq. (44)), only a single overall correlation time (œÑc) is required, which depends on both the macromolecule rotational correlation time (œÑr) and the electron spin relaxation time (œÑs) (Eq. (45)). If œÑs ‚â´ œÑr (e.g. nitroxide spin labels (Bernini et al. 2009)), then the value of œÑs can be ignored, and œÑc is just simply œÑr. However, if œÑs is of the order of, or shorter than, œÑr (e.g. paramagnetic metal ions), then the value of œÑs must be taken into account. Under rigid SB assumptions, œÑc can be calculated directly from the ratio
of transverse and longitudinal PRE values (Iwahara et al. 2003):

œÑc

