(Eqs. (82)‚Äì(84)) in MATLAB. The y-axis gives the ratio of the peak intensity measured in the presence of a CW RF B1 field (Isat) over the peak intensity measured for a reference experiment in the absence of the saturation field (Iref). The x-axis gives the frequency offset of the applied B1 field. Note that the units are (a) in Hz for the CEST profiles, but are (b) in kHz for the DEST profiles, where the x-axis has been expanded almost 50 fold to
